From: <you>
Subject: [PATCH] graphics: make gr_deinit() idempotent (fix double free on WM close)

gr_deinit() is registered via atexit() in gr_init() AND called explicitly
from the WM-delete path in x.c (xclient -> ttyhangup -> gr_deinit -> exit).
So closing the window runs it twice: exit(0) re-invokes it through atexit.

The images half is already double-call safe (guarded by `images` and nulled),
but kv_destroy(next_redraw_times) is `free((v).a)` with no null afterward, so
the second call frees the same block again:

    free(): double free detected in tcache 2

Guard the whole function with a one-shot static flag so it is safe regardless
of how many entry points invoke it. (Exiting the shell normally only triggers
the atexit path once, which is why this only showed up on window close.)
---
--- a/graphics.c
+++ b/graphics.c
@@ -2146,6 +2146,12 @@
 
 /// Deinitialize the graphics module.
 void gr_deinit() {
+	// gr_deinit may be called both explicitly (e.g. on WM close) and again
+	// via atexit() during exit(); guard so the frees below run only once.
+	static int deinitialized = 0;
+	if (deinitialized)
+		return;
+	deinitialized = 1;
 	// Remove the cache dir.
 	remove(cache_dir);
 	kv_destroy(next_redraw_times);
